---An artist needs an empty canvas, not paint by numbers. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.premiernet.net/~chandler/images/newmaclogo3.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gwenllianmacrhuad>Gwenllian MacRhuad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#330000>(7/20/01 1:25:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Poll out of boredom</span><hr size=1> Try not thinking of it as art, it's more like improvisational theater, roleplaying is.  It sounds to me like you have roleplaying and getting everything exactly how you want it mixed up.  I wonder how far DeNiro would have gotten if he said, &quot;I can't play this role, I don't like your backstory!&quot;.  We are not artists here, we are not the architects of this world.  We are poor, simple thespians acting out our roles in the great theater which is Norrath.  In some ways I concur with your sentiments, no MMORPG has yet to ever facilitate what I consider roleplaying to be.  However, I don't lay the blame on the programmers, conceptual artists, story writers, and other staff members of the companies which produce them; I lay it on the hordes of prepubescent mongoloids who insist on being contrary and degrading those of us who do roleplay.  And as far as UO being more conducive to RP, you must have played a different game than I did.  I do not remember a game of roleplaying, but rather one where my poor tailor couldn't even kill a rabbit for his hide without being overrun by Psychodewd and his legion of red named thugs.  Nevertheless I founded a guild built on roleplaying and we did just that.  My point is that whining over the game makes no sense, no gaming atmosphere, backstory, or rules system is going to be precisely as you want it unless you are the one who designed it (and for me at least, that doesn't even always help).  Asked my opinion I would say EQ sucks, I do not like the game.  However, I don't roleplay with the game.  I roleplay with the people in it, most notably my clan. And despite the fact that I hate how Verant designed a game which requires camping and raiding to achieve the higher levels and upper end gear (In fact I despise all the upper end gear itself), I still play it my way.  I fight green critters, wander about and take pictures of the landscape, and chat with my friends.  I am Gwenllian the Bloody Handed, born of Halfling stock but raised in Halas.  Did the game let me take the last name &quot;the Bloody Handed&quot;? No.  Did it let me start in Halas? No.  BUt that doesn't mean I can't pretend I did, I can call myself what I wish and claim what lineage I may.  Will I ever make 60th Level and have my epic weapon? Probably not. Does that bother me? Not in the least, wouldn't bother me if I stayed 23rd for the rest of my life and never got a better weapon then the one which I'm now toting about now.  In any case, I've gone on far longer than I initially intended to and will leave it at that.  Just my view from down here.<br>
<br>
For Halas! For MacLear!<br>
Gwenllian MacRhuad of the Clan MacLear<br>
Halfling Warrior of the 23rd Season<br>
Aspiring Blueberry (very slowly Aspiring) <br>
