<br>
---When I stated that UO was more condusive to roleplay, I didn't mean to infer that the players actually participated in it. I meant that the game's soil was plowed and ready for a roleplayer. If I wanted to roleplay a swindler, I could. Mad wizard? Sure. Displaced halfling... with some effort. Former Necormancer, since resurrected, amnesiatic, dark-skinned, bald guy that lives with a clan of barbarians? Done it. =) It was the LACK of in-game backstory that facilitated this. In EQ, I've only met two people who were in character almost the whole time.<br>
<br>
---I wasn't aware I was whining, and I'm sorry if it came across that way. I wouldn't infer that EQ totally stifles RP, as you and I have both &quot;made do&quot; with the forks Verant gave us. I've always championed and lampooned EQ for what it was... and is. A game for gamers. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.premiernet.net/~chandler/images/newmaclogo3.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uhyfaidd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyfaidd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#330000>(7/27/01 7:13:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Poll out of boredom</span><hr size=1> What RP games require is a GM that the players know and who knows the players that can &quot;adjust&quot; the game to meet whatever the playing group requires. So if a monk wants to be a barbarian, the NPC reaction is adjusted. If a halfling is raised in Halas then everyone there knows it, rare enough for nearly everyone in that small city to have heard about it afterall. As that GM I would have required MacLear to have proper adoption cermonies etc. A world with lots of backstory can work for RP. Golanthra, (RuneQuest and Hero Wars) has a massive backstory, which my not very RP players loved for all the guides it gave them and my Massive RP loved for all the options they could do. BUT the GM (me) adjusted the world for them too. MMOGs will be fine when they have 1 admin for every 10 players. LOL <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=1106.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboar